===2020 census===
As of the [[2020 United States census|2020 census]], Roseville had a population of 39, with 8 households and 8 families. The median age was 29.2 years. 17.9% of residents were under the age of 18 and 17.9% were 65 years of age or older. 25.6% of residents were under the age of 20; 23.1% were from 20 to 24; 12.8% were from 25 to 44; and 20.5% were from 45 to 64. The gender makeup of the community was 59.0% male and 41.0% female. For every 100 females there were 143.8 males, and for every 100 females age 18 and over there were 128.6 males age 18 and over.<ref name="Census2020DP">{{cite web|title=2020 Decennial Census Demographic Profile (DP1)|url=https://api.census.gov/data/2020/dec/dp?get=NAME,DP1_0021P,DP1_0024P,DP1_0025C,DP1_0049C,DP1_0045C,DP1_0069C,DP1_0073C,DP1_0125P,DP1_0126P,DP1_0129P,DP1_0133P,DP1_0137P,DP1_0138P,DP1_0139P,DP1_0141P,DP1_0142P,DP1_0143P,DP1_0145P,DP1_0146P,DP1_0147C,DP1_0148C,DP1_0149C,DP1_0156C,DP1_0157C,DP1_0158C,DP1_0159P,DP1_0160P&for=place%3A68800&in=state%3A19|website=United States Census Bureau|year=2021|access-date=May 2, 2026|df=mdy}}</ref><ref name="Census2020PL">{{cite web|title=2020 Decennial Census Redistricting Data (Public Law 94-171)|url=https://api.census.gov/data/2020/dec/pl?get=NAME,P1_001N,P1_003N,P1_004N,P1_005N,P1_006N,P1_007N,P1_008N,P1_009N,P2_001N,P2_002N,H1_001N,H1_002N&for=place%3A68800&in=state%3A19|website=United States Census Bureau|year=2021|access-date=May 2, 2026|df=mdy}}</ref>

All residents lived in rural areas. The [[population density]] was 10.6 inhabitants per square mile (4.1/km<sup>2</sup>).<ref name="Census2020DHC">{{cite web|title=2020 Decennial Census Demographic and Housing Characteristics (DHC)|url=https://api.census.gov/data/2020/dec/dhc?get=NAME,P2_002N,P2_003N&for=place%3A68800&in=state%3A19|website=United States Census Bureau|year=2023|access-date=May 2, 2026|df=mdy}}</ref><ref name="Census2020DP"/>

There were 8 households, of which 12.5% had children under the age of 18 living in them. Of all households, 87.5% were married-couple households, 0.0% were cohabitating couple households, 12.5% were households with a male householder and no spouse or partner present, and 0.0% were households with a female householder and no spouse or partner present. Non-family households accounted for 0.0% of all households. About 0.0% of all households were made up of individuals and 0.0% had someone living alone who was 65 years of age or older.<ref name="Census2020DP"/>

There were 17 housing units, with an average density of 4.6 per square mile (1.8/km<sup>2</sup>), of which 52.9% were vacant. The homeowner vacancy rate was 20.0% and the rental vacancy rate was 0.0%.<ref name="Census2020DP"/>

